e><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uaelspear.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aelspear</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Patron</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/11/02 9:53:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ftheshanksgeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=953.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A letter to Wotan</span><hr size=1> <br>Hehe she also switched from scout to cleric.  :-)<br><br>-Elsebet <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ushieldofpurity.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shield of Purity</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Patron</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/11/02 5:12:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ftheshanksgeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=953.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A letter to Wotan</span><hr size=1> Hehe,<br><br>yea yea,<br><br>Well, the true story is this, I quit the scout because to me and in my opinion, it is almost impossible for someone who knows nobody in Albion to level a scout past 23. Mine got that high, and after that, its very very hard to find a group. People think, why get a scout? We can always get a armsman or a paladin or a mercenary. I tried for a long time to level, but quickly found myself regulated to running around Thidranki. When I got kicked out, I tried for about a day in places like darkness falls and catacombs to find a group. That didn't work, Erya quickly went to the back burners and I went to a Friar. My Friar leveled quick, and I do mean, quickly,and I was a different Friar.<br><br>My Friar was rejuv based, and the people that I met quickly asked, why didnt you just go cleric with that high of a rejuvenation? I didnt have an answer for that, so I gave it a shot. I learned quickly why I chose healer in midgard was because im good as a role as a healer. No, I didnt follow the road of stupidity like some and go smite, if I wanted to be a wizard I would have been one.<br><br>As for how is Albion? It's hard to say honestly, it is. After Albion lost its backbone of 5 relics, things quickly went bad. Fingers started getting pointed, people yelled at others, alliances fell apart and so forth. Some of the stronger alliances stayed together and began planning, and thinking ahead to days to come. But now, we have the problem of like before when ALBION owned all the relics, people are leaving to join the winning team. Most of them are the younger generation, those who just joined to see that, wow, I picked the losing team. Quickly a delete was made and a re-role at that to the sunny shores of Midgard. <br><br>Will I go you ask? No, I didnt leave last time for the relics, I left because, Midgard didnt fit the part in my soul that was with this game. When I played Everquest, I could have been a Shank, I could have went Barbarian rogue, but instead I went human rogue. I never fancied myself as a barbarian or a norse or a troll, I fancied myself, human, hence, Briton. Im a healer by heart, I fix that which is broken and mend that which is torn, hence, cleric (and a friar that was horrid at fighting). I for one, will always be a Shank in mind. I grew up with a lot of you, and lived the better part of my Everquest life fighting beside you. When DAoC came out, many of you saw, I didn't go to Midgard to be a norse, I went to be a Shank. Because, my life as gaming has always revolved around the elimination and destruction of mutants in whatever form they may come from. &lt;Shield of Purity&gt;<br><br>I joined Midgard to find myself fighting besides trolls, and kobolds and dwarves, the same people I was killing in Everquest I was helping here. I was disgusted and hurt to see this, and quickly, I went to Albion to fight for the human race. <br>I went to Albion, to continue my crusade against the races of mutants who would sweep into my fair Albion to hurt her and destroy her. I apologize that you norse happen to get in the way of this. <p><center><font size = 5>Erya Kelrath<p> GM - Umbra Eversoris<p> A Roleplaying Guild in<p><img src ="http://www.darkageofcamelot.com/images/albion_header.jpg"></font></center></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/ftheshanksgeneraldiscussion.showPrevMessage?topicID=953.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/ftheshanksgeneraldiscussion.showNextMessage?topicID=953.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ftheshanksgeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=953.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/~fricka/shanks/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ftheshanksgeneraldiscussion.emailToFriend?topicID=953.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ftheshanksgeneraldiscussion.threadControl?topicID=953.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/~fricka/shanks/delete.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ftheshanksgeneraldiscussion.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=953.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ftheshanksgeneraldiscussion.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=953.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receivi